'''Gactimus''' was a religious figure with a large following among the [[Insectoid/Legends|insectoid]] [[Tritonite]]s of the [[Triton/Legends|Triton]] [[Moon/Legends|Moons]]. Even the best religious scholars of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] disagreed about who or what Gactimus was.<ref name="The Essential Atlas">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> Gactimus's teachings banned entertainment and stimulants of any kind, making the [[Triton Moons]] notorious as being "dead".

Tritonite acolytes were a common site around the galaxy, handing out free tracts on Gactimus encouraging individual enlightenment.

==Behind the scenes==
Gactimus was created by [[Jason Fry]] for ''[[Zygerrian Takedown]]''. Fry confirmed Gactimus was a religious figure, and indicated that Gactimus will be further developed in ''[[The Essential Atlas]]''.<ref name="JCF">{{JCFCite|url=posts/28148585|board=Literature|thread=The Essential Atlas and Galactic Cartography: Official Discussion|user=[[Jason Fry|jasonfry]]|date=2008-03-02|time=2:59 PM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200802092323/https://boards.theforce.net/threads/the-essential-atlas-and-galactic-cartography-official-discussion.21938930/page-51}}</ref> Following these mentions, ''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'' erroneously interpreted [[Gactimus (moon)|Gactimus]] as being a [[Moon/Legends|moon]] of Triton.<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|I|306|Gactimus}}</ref>

